%% Pattern B: Broadcast Fan-Out Sequence - v2
%% Key changes from v1:
%% - atomic claim_task replaces acquire_lock (GPT-5: race condition fix)
%% - partition_id + correlation_id in all events (all 4 reviewers)
%% - task registry in os-state.json tracks expected vs completed (not bus counting)
%% - ORCHESTRATOR failover if it crashes mid-fan-out (Gemini)
%% - INNER_AGENT uses short TTL leased locks with PID file (all 4 reviewers)

sequenceDiagram
  autonumber

  participant ORC as ORCHESTRATOR
  participant K as kernel.py
  participant STATE as os-state.json
  participant BUS as events.jsonl
  participant IA1 as INNER_AGENT_1
  participant IA2 as INNER_AGENT_2
  participant IA3 as INNER_AGENT_3
  participant PEER as PEER_AGENT

  Note over ORC,PEER: ORCHESTRATOR registers fan-out job in task registry

  ORC->>K: claim_task - job_id, expected: 3, partitions: skill-A, skill-B, skill-C
  K->>STATE: create task registry entry, completed: 0
  K-->>ORC: job registered

  ORC->>K: emit task.assigned broadcast - correlation_id: job_id, partitions listed
  K->>BUS: append broadcast

  Note over PEER: PEER_AGENT monitors ORCHESTRATOR heartbeat throughout

  Note over IA1,IA3: All INNER_AGENTs wake concurrently via Claude CLI

  par IA1 claims partition
    IA1->>K: claim_task --partition skill-A --agent IA1 --ttl 120
    K->>STATE: mark skill-A claimed by IA1, write PID
    K-->>IA1: claimed - short TTL lease active
  and IA2 claims partition
    IA2->>K: claim_task --partition skill-B --agent IA2 --ttl 120
    K->>STATE: mark skill-B claimed by IA2, write PID
    K-->>IA2: claimed
  and IA3 claims partition
    IA3->>K: claim_task --partition skill-C --agent IA3 --ttl 120
    K->>STATE: mark skill-C claimed by IA3, write PID
    K-->>IA3: claimed
  end

  Note over IA1,IA3: Each INNER_AGENT executes independently

  par IA1 executes
    IA1->>IA1: pipe skill through audit prompt, collect findings
    IA1->>K: emit task.complete - partition_id: skill-A, correlation_id: job_id
    K->>BUS: append
    K->>STATE: increment completed counter, mark skill-A done
    K->>STATE: release lease on skill-A partition
  and IA2 executes
    IA2->>IA2: pipe skill through audit prompt, collect findings
    IA2->>K: emit task.complete - partition_id: skill-B, correlation_id: job_id
    K->>BUS: append
    K->>STATE: increment completed counter, mark skill-B done
    K->>STATE: release lease on skill-B partition
  and IA3 executes
    IA3->>IA3: pipe skill through audit prompt, collect findings
    IA3->>K: emit task.complete - partition_id: skill-C, correlation_id: job_id
    K->>BUS: append
    K->>STATE: increment completed counter, mark skill-C done
    K->>STATE: release lease on skill-C partition
  end

  Note over ORC: ORCHESTRATOR waits via task registry - not by counting bus events

  ORC->>K: wait_for_event --job job_id --until completed == expected --timeout 300
  Note over ORC: Python blocks - LLM not polling

  alt all 3 complete before timeout
    K-->>ORC: job complete - Python unblocks
    ORC->>STATE: read all findings from task registry
    ORC->>ORC: apply valid rewrites, git commit
    ORC->>K: emit fix.applied - all skills, method: fan-out, correlation_id: job_id
    K->>BUS: append
  else ORCHESTRATOR crashes before merge
    Note over PEER: PEER_AGENT detects missed ORCHESTRATOR heartbeats
    PEER->>K: claim_role --role ORCHESTRATOR --correlation-id job_id
    K->>STATE: transfer job ownership to PEER
    PEER->>STATE: read completed partitions, resume merge
    PEER->>ORC: emit role.claimed - PEER assumed orchestrator for job_id
  end

  Note over ORC,PEER: Fan-out complete. Wall-clock equals max of all agents, not sum.
